source.name: Annual Federal Government Energy Use and Costs by Agency, 1975 - 2007
source.description: Data set presents historical energy use in native units and billion site-delivered Btu and costs (in 2010 dollars) aggregated at the top-tier Federal agency level for the fiscal years 1975 through 2007.  Data is grouped into two main end-use sectors, facility and mobility energy use, and is further broken down by energy type, electricity, natural gas, petroleum types, coal, steam, and others.
